# Supabase and data layer

Read **agents.md** "How data should work" and **`.cursor/rules/workspace-packages.mdc`**.

## Responsibilities

- **Browser:** `@minute-menus/supabase-service` (facade: `services/supabaseService.ts`) resolves restaurant context from session (owner) or slug/id (customer). All UI reads/writes go through `supabaseService`.
- **Server API routes:** `lib/supabase-admin.ts` only; service role env var never in Vite client bundle.
- **Schema:** `supabase/schema.sql` defines tables, RLS, RPCs — update schema, `@minute-menus/types/db`, and service mappings together.

## Package split

| Concern | Package |
|---|---|
| Service class + restaurant context | `@minute-menus/supabase-service` |
| Menu upsert/sync/delete | `@minute-menus/menu-persistence` |
| Meal plan rows + dish links | `@minute-menus/meal-plan-persistence` |
| Analytics builders (pure) | `@minute-menus/metrics` |
| Domain + DB types | `@minute-menus/types`, `@minute-menus/types/db` |

Inject the browser client via `createSupabaseService(supabase)` — no module-level Supabase import inside the package.

## Menu persistence

`saveMenu` is a full sync: upsert all categories/dishes, delete anything not in the payload. Use explicit id lists for deletes. Throw via `@minute-menus/errors`.

## Schema changes workflow

Update schema file → push via db:push or SQL editor → sync `packages/types/src/database.types.ts` → extend `@minute-menus/types` and supabase-service mappers → update UI field mapping.

Do not extend mockData.ts for new features.
